 {"id":"remote_compilation_helper-cs7","title":"Scheduled Self-Test Runs","description":"## Problem
Self-tests currently only run on-demand via `rch self-test`. There is no automated verification that remote compilation continues to work correctly over time.

Issues that could emerge silently:
- Rust toolchain version mismatch between local and worker
- Worker disk corruption
- Network issues causing incomplete transfers
- Configuration drift

## Solution
Add scheduled self-test capability that runs verification periodically.

### Configuration
```toml
[self_test]
# Enable scheduled self-tests
enabled = true

# Schedule: cron expression or interval
schedule = "0 3 * * *"  # Daily at 3am
# or
interval = "24h"

# Which workers to test
workers = "all"  # or specific: ["gpu-server-1", "cpu-server-2"]

# Action on failure
on_failure = "alert"  # or "disable_worker", "alert_and_disable"

# Retry failed tests
retry_count = 3
retry_delay = "5m"
```

### CLI Control
```bash
# View self-test schedule
$ rch self-test status
Scheduled self-tests: enabled
  Schedule: Daily at 3:00 AM
  Last run: 2024-01-15 03:00:00 (all passed)
  Next run: 2024-01-16 03:00:00

# Manually trigger scheduled test
$ rch self-test --scheduled
Running scheduled self-test for all workers...

# View self-test history
$ rch self-test history
DATE        TIME     WORKERS  PASSED  FAILED  DURATION
2024-01-15  03:00    3        3       0       45s
2024-01-14  03:00    3        3       0       42s
2024-01-13  03:00    3        2       1       38s
            └─ gpu-server-1 failed: hash mismatch (auto-disabled, re-enabled after fix)
```

### Auto-Recovery Actions

#### on_failure = "alert"
Only send alert, take no action:
```
⚠️  Self-test failed for gpu-server-1
    Reason: Binary hash mismatch
    Local:  a1b2c3d4...
    Remote: e5f6g7h8...

    Run `rch self-test --worker=gpu-server-1 --verbose` for details
```

#### on_failure = "disable_worker"
Automatically disable failing worker:
```
⚠️  Self-test failed for gpu-server-1
    Worker automatically disabled
    Reason: Binary hash mismatch

    After investigation, run:
    rch workers enable gpu-server-1
```

#### on_failure = "alert_and_disable"
Both alert and disable (most conservative).

